<title>USA: BankAmerica, VISA to start Internet test.</title>
<headline>BankAmerica, VISA to start Internet test.</headline>
<dateline>SAN FRANCISCO 1997-05-15</dateline>
<text>
<p>BankAmerica Corp and Visa International said they will start testing stored-value chip card transactions on the Internet this summer.</p>
<p>Employees of Bank of America and Visa will participate in the test using reloadable Visa Cash stored-value chip cards and their personal computers to purchase goods from participating merchants on the World Wide Web.</p>
<p>Broderbund Software Inc, CardMart Greetings and Newsletter Technologies Inc will be the first merchants to participate in the six-month pilot, with several additional companies expected to follow.</p>
